// Media plane for mod_open_switch.
//
// Per-call bidirectional audio streams from FreeSWITCH (via media bug) to
// an external service: TTS, STT, voicebot, AMD, etc. The module is the
// gRPC CLIENT here (it initiates the stream); the external service is the
// SERVER.
//
// Design:
//   - One stream per (channel_uuid, purpose) pair. A single call may have
//     several streams open simultaneously (e.g. STT + TTS + recording-relay).
//   - The first client→server message MUST be a StreamStart; subsequent
//     messages are AudioFrame. The first server→client message is
//     StreamReady; subsequent messages are AudioFrame or Control.
//   - Cancellation is propagated bidirectionally: gRPC cancel on either
//     side -> media bug removed and call audio falls back to silence.
//   - On call hangup, the module half-closes the client send stream and
//     waits up to `drain_timeout_ms` for the server to finish before
//     forcibly cancelling.

